Six fixes addressing the staff+student attendance audit:

B2 — Status enum mismatch.
  attendances.status was missing 'holiday' that staff_attendances had
  and the mobile UI offered. Added migration adding 'holiday' to the
  enum + accepted in both AttendanceController validation and
  MobileApiController validation.

B3 — Attendance % formula was inconsistent across the app.
  Five different formulas for the same metric. Standardised on
  (present + late*0.5 + half_day*0.5) / total — late and half_day
  count as half-credit. Touched:
    Api/MobileApiController.php (teacher branch, parent branch,
      stats helper, attendance summary)
    Api/Mobile/AttendanceController.php
    Export/AttendanceExportController.php (note: still no half_day
      column in this exporter, applied to late only)

B4 — Staff monthly report calendar misalignment.
  StaffAttendanceController::report() was building day keys with
  \$byDate->first()?->date->year — so a staff member whose only
  record was on day 28 had the entire calendar built around that
  one record's year/month. Now uses \$startDate->year/month
  (the requested month) directly.

M1 — Staff attendance scope gap.
  staff-attendance.index/store/report routes were on the default
  school.management middleware, which lets teachers through. Now
  gated by school.management:admin_only — only admin / school_admin
  / principal / super_admin can mark or view all staff attendance.

M3 — Dashboard was missing student_unmarked_today.
  Mirrors the staff_unmarked_today field added last commit. The
  attendance bento tile on the dashboard now shows "Not marked yet"
  in amber when 0 records exist for the day, and "X unmarked" along
  with present/absent counts when partial.

M4 — Parent absence notifications were opt-in.
  AttendanceController::store() only fired notifications when the
  client passed send_notifications=true. Now defaults to ON via the
  new school setting notifications_v2.attendance_auto_notify (true
  by default). Schools that don't want auto-notify can flip the
  setting; clients can still send_notifications=false to opt-out
  per-request.

M2 (auto-fill on declared holidays) intentionally deferred — it's
bigger work needing a daily scheduled job, and the enum addition
above is a prerequisite anyway.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
